quran[227]{c,v,t}:
  26,1,S. M. (Ta. Sin. Mim)
  26,2,These are verses of the clear (and clarifying) book
  26,3,You may kill yourself with grief because they do not become believers
  26,4,"If We want, We send down a sign to them from the sky so their necks bend in humility for it"
  26,5,"No new reminder comes to them from the beneficent, unless they turn away from it"
  26,6,"They have denied, so the news of what they used to ridicule it is going to come to them"
  26,7,"Or did they not look at the earth, that how many of all kind of splendid plants did We grow in it"
  26,8,"Indeed there is a sign in that, and most of them are not believers"
  26,9,"And indeed your Master, He is the powerful and the merciful"
  26,10,"And (remember) when your Master called Moses: go to the wrongdoing people"
  26,11,"people of Pharaoh, (and ask) would they not be cautious (of God)"
  26,12,"He said: my Master, I am afraid that they deny me"
  26,13,"and my chest becomes tight and my tongue stutters, so send (the message) to Aaron"
  26,14,"And they have a charge against me, so I am afraid that they kill me"
  26,15,"He (God) said: no way, you two go with Our signs, We are with you, listening"
  26,16,"So you two go to Pharaoh and say: indeed we are messengers of the Master of Human kind"
  26,17,send the children of Israel with us
  26,18,"He (Pharaoh) said: did we not bring you up among us as a child, and you stayed among us for years of your life"
  26,19,"And you did your work that you did (and committed murder), and you are of the ungrateful ones"
  26,20,"He (Moses) said: I did it while I was of the lost ones (from the right path)"
  26,21,"then I ran away from you because I was afraid of you, then my Master gave me wisdom and made me of the messengers"
  26,22,"And that is a favor that you tell me off about it, that you enslaved children of Israel (and you did not enslave or kill me)"
  26,23,"Pharaoh said: and what is Master of humankind"
  26,24,"He (Moses) said: Master of the skies and the earth and whatever between them, if you are sure"
  26,25,"He said to those around him: do you not hear (what he says)"
  26,26,"He (Moses) said: your Master and Master of your forefathers"
  26,27,"He said (to the others): your messenger, the one who was sent to you is certainly crazy"
  26,28,"He (Moses) said: Master of the east and the west and whatever between them, if you understand"
  26,29,"He said: if you take any god other than me, I shall make you of the prisoners"
  26,30,"He (Moses) said: even if I bring you something obvious"
  26,31,"He said: then bring it, if you are of the truthful ones"
  26,32,So he threw his cane and it immediately was a visible serpent
  26,33,"And he took out his hand, and it was white to the viewers"
  26,34,"He said to the assembly around him: indeed this is a knowledgeable (and skillful) magician"
  26,35,"He wants to drive you out of your land with his magic, so what do you instruct"
  26,36,"They said: put him and his brother off (for a while) and send gatherers to the cities"
  26,37,to bring you every skillful magician
  26,38,So the magicians were collected for an appointment on a known day
  26,39,"And people were told: would you come together"
  26,40,We may follow the magicians if they are the winners
  26,41,"So when the magicians came, they said to Pharaoh: is there a reward for us if we are the winners"
  26,42,"He said: yes, and then you will certainly be among the close ones"
  26,43,"Moses said to them: throw what you are throwing"
  26,44,"So they threw their ropes and their canes and they said: by Pharaoh’s power, we shall be the winners"
  26,45,"Then Moses threw his cane, and it immediately swallowed whatever they faked"
  26,46,"So the magicians fell, prostrating (and showing humbleness)"
  26,47,"They said: we believed in the Master of Human kind"
  26,48,Master of Moses and Aaron
  26,49,"He (Pharaoh) said: did you believe in him before I give you permission? He is certainly your superior, the one who taught you the magic, and you will certainly know that I shall cut off your hands and feet on opposite side, and I shall crucify you all"
  26,50,"They said: no problem, indeed we are returners to our Master"
  26,51,Indeed we hope that our Master forgives us our faults because we are the first of the believers
  26,52,"And We revealed to Moses: travel with My servants by night, indeed you will be followed"
  26,53,So Pharaoh sent gatherers to the cities
  26,54,(saying) indeed these are a small group
  26,55,and they certainly angered us
  26,56,and we are all certainly alert (and ready)
  26,57,So We drove them out of gardens and springs
  26,58,and treasures and honorable position
  26,59,"That is how it was, and We left them as inheritance for children of Israel"
  26,60,So they (Pharaoh’s army) followed them at sunrise
  26,61,"So when the two crowds saw each other, companions of Moses said: indeed we will be caught"
  26,62,"He (Moses) said: no way, indeed my Master is with me, He is going to guide me"
  26,63,"And We revealed to Moses to strike the sea with your cane. So it opened up, and each side became like a great mountain"
  26,64,And We brought the others (Pharaoh’s army) near there
  26,65,And We saved Moses and those with him altogether
  26,66,Then We drowned the others
  26,67,"Indeed there is a sign in that, and most of them are not believers"
  26,68,And indeed your Master is the powerful and the merciful
  26,69,And read Abraham’s story to them
  26,70,"When he said to his father and his people: what do you serve"
  26,71,"They said: we serve idols, and we continue to be devoted to them"
  26,72,"He said: do they hear you when you call on them"
  26,73,Or do they benefit you or harm you
  26,74,"They said: no, but we found our fathers doing like this"
  26,75,"He said: did you think what you were serving"
  26,76,you and your forefathers
  26,77,"Indeed they are my enemies, except the Master of Human kind"
  26,78,"the One who created me, and He guides me"
  26,79,and the One who gives me food and gives me drink
  26,80,"and when I get sick, then He heals me"
  26,81,"and the One who make me die, then He makes me alive"
  26,82,"and the One who, I hope that He forgives my mistakes on the judgment day"
  26,83,"My Master, give me wisdom and join me with the righteous"
  26,84,and give me a good name on the tongue of the later ones (and future generations)
  26,85,and make me among inheritors of garden of the delight
  26,86,"and forgive my father, indeed he is of the lost ones"
  26,87,and do not humiliate me on a day that they are raised
  26,88,a day that wealth and children have no benefit
  26,89,except anyone who brings a sound (and pure) heart to God
  26,90,And the garden is brought near for those who control themselves
  26,91,And the hellfire is made apparent to the misled ones
  26,92,"And it is said to them: where are what you were serving"
  26,93,other than God? Can they help you or help themselves
  26,94,So they and the misled ones are thrown headfirst into it (hellfire)
  26,95,"and troops of Iblis (Satan), altogether"
  26,96,"And while they dispute about it, they say"
  26,97,by God that we were in an obvious error
  26,98,when we made you equal to the Master of Human kind
  26,99,And no one misguided us except the guilty ones
  26,100,"So, we do not have any mediators"
  26,101,and no true friend
  26,102,"And if there was a return for us (to live again), then we would become of the believers"
  26,103,"Indeed there is a sign in that, and most of them are not believers"
  26,104,And indeed your Master is the powerful and the merciful
  26,105,People of Noah denied the messengers
  26,106,"When their brother Noah said to them: would you not be cautious (of God)"
  26,107,I am an honest messenger for you
  26,108,so be cautious of God and obey me
  26,109,"And I do not ask you for any wage, for my wage is only responsibility of the Master of Human kind"
  26,110,so be cautious of God and obey me
  26,111,"They said: should we believe in you while the meanest (and the worst) follow you"
  26,112,"He said: I have no knowledge of what they used to do"
  26,113,"Their account is only upon my Master, if you realize"
  26,114,And I do not drive away the believers
  26,115,I am only a clear warner
  26,116,"They said: Noah, if you do not stop, you shall become among the stoned ones"
  26,117,"He said: my Master, indeed my people denied me"
  26,118,"so judge decisively (or open an opening) between me and them, and save me and anyone who is with me of the believers"
  26,119,So We saved him and anyone with him in the loaded Ark
  26,120,Then afterward We drowned the rest
  26,121,"Indeed there is a sign in that, and most of them are not believers"
  26,122,And your Master is certainly powerful and merciful
  26,123,(People of) Aad denied the messengers
  26,124,"when their brother Hud said to them: would you not be cautious (of God)"
  26,125,I am an honest messenger for you
  26,126,so be cautious of God and obey me
  26,127,"And I do not ask you for any wage, for my wage is only responsibility of the Master of Human kind"
  26,128,Do you build a sign on every high place to fool around
  26,129,And you take up castles that you may live forever
  26,130,"And when you attack, you attack as tyrants"
  26,131,So be cautious of God and obey me
  26,132,And be cautious of the One who helped you with what you know
  26,133,He helped you with livestock and children
  26,134,and gardens and springs
  26,135,Indeed I am afraid of the punishment of a great day upon you
  26,136,"They said: it is the same to us whether you advise or are not of the advisors"
  26,137,this is only character of the earlier ones
  26,138,and we will not be punished
  26,139,"So they denied him, then We destroyed them. Indeed there is a sign in that, and most of them are not believers"
  26,140,And indeed your Master is the powerful and the merciful
  26,141,(People of) Thamud denied the messengers
  26,142,"when their brother Salih said to them: would you not be cautious (of God)"
  26,143,I am an honest messenger for you
  26,144,so be cautious of God and obey me
  26,145,"And I do not ask you for any wage, for my wage is only responsibility of the Master of Human kind"
  26,146,Would you be left safe (and secure) in what is here
  26,147,In gardens and springs
  26,148,and plantations and a palm tree with its ripe (and delicious) fruit cluster
  26,149,and houses you skillfully carve out of the mountains
  26,150,So be cautious of God and obey me
  26,151,and do not obey order of the excessive ones
  26,152,those who commit corruption on the earth and do not reform
  26,153,"They said: you are only of the bewitched ones"
  26,154,"you are only a human being like us, so bring a miracle if you are of the truthful ones"
  26,155,"He said: this is a (female) camel, she has (a portion of) drink and you have your (portion of) drink, on a known day"
  26,156,And do not touch her with harm otherwise the punishment of a great day takes you
  26,157,"So they killed her, then they became regretful"
  26,158,"Then the punishment took them. Indeed there is a sign in that, and most of them are not believers"
  26,159,And indeed your Master is the powerful and the merciful
  26,160,People of Lot denied the messengers
  26,161,"when their brother Lot said to them: would you not be cautious (of God)"
  26,162,I am an honest messenger for you
  26,163,so be cautious of God and obey me
  26,164,"And I do not ask you for any wage, for my wage is only responsibility of the Master of Human kind"
  26,165,Do you approach the males among humankind
  26,166,"And you leave what your Master created for you as your wives? No, but you are people who exceed the limits"
  26,167,"They said: Lot, if you do not stop, you shall be of those driven out"
  26,168,"He said: indeed I am of those who despise your action"
  26,169,"My Master, save me and my family from what they do"
  26,170,So We saved him and his family altogether
  26,171,except an old woman (his wife who was) among those staying behind
  26,172,Then We destroyed the others
  26,173,"And We poured down a rain on them, and it was an awful rain on those who were warned"
  26,174,"Indeed there is a sign in that, and most of them are not believers"
  26,175,And indeed your Master is the powerful and the merciful
  26,176,The inhabitants of the woods (people of Midian) denied the messengers
  26,177,"when Shu'aib said to them: would you not be cautious (of God)"
  26,178,I am an honest messenger for you
  26,179,so be cautious of God and obey me
  26,180,"And I do not ask you for any wage, for my wage is only responsibility of the Master of Human kind"
  26,181,"Give the full measure, and do not be of those who give less (than due)"
  26,182,and weigh with accurate scale
  26,183,and do not shortchange people their things and do not do mischief on the earth as corruptors
  26,184,And be cautious of the One who created you and the earlier generations
  26,185,"They said: indeed you are of the bewitched ones"
  26,186,"you are only a human being like us, and we think you are among the liars"
  26,187,"So, make pieces of the sky fall on us, if you are of the truthful ones"
  26,188,"He said: my Master knows best what you do"
  26,189,"So they denied him, then the punishment of day of the covering clouds (of fire) took them. Indeed it was the punishment of a great day"
  26,190,"Indeed there is a sign in that, and most of them are not believers"
  26,191,And indeed your Master is the powerful and the merciful
  26,192,And it (Quran) is certainly a sending down by the Master of Human kind
  26,193,The honest spirit (Gabriel) came down with it
  26,194,to your heart so that you be of the warners
  26,195,in clear Arabic language
  26,196,And indeed it is in the scriptures of the earlier ones
  26,197,Is it not a sign for them that the knowledgeable children of Israel know it
  26,198,And if We had sent it down to someone of the non-Arabs
  26,199,"and he had read it to them, they would not have been believers in it"
  26,200,That is how We insert/pass it through the hearts of guilty ones
  26,201,they would not believe in it until they see the painful punishment
  26,202,And it comes to them suddenly while they do not realize
  26,203,"Then they say: may we be given a delay"
  26,204,Do they still want to rush Our punishment
  26,205,So did you think that if We make them enjoy for some years
  26,206,then what they were promised (the punishment) comes to them
  26,207,what they were made to enjoy would not be of any use to them
  26,208,We did not destroy any town (or population) unless there were warners for it
  26,209,"to remind, and We were not unjust"
  26,210,And the devils did not come down with it (Quran)
  26,211,"It is not appropriate for them, and they can not"
  26,212,Indeed they are blocked from the hearing (of it)
  26,213,"So do not call on another god with God, otherwise you become of the punished ones"
  26,214,And warn your closest family (and tribe members)
  26,215,And lower your wing (and be kind) for anyone who follows you among the believers
  26,216,"And If they disobey you, then say: I am clear of what you do"
  26,217,"And put your trust in the powerful, the merciful"
  26,218,The One who sees you when you stand (for prayer)
  26,219,and your movement among those who prostrate (and show humbleness)
  26,220,Indeed He hears all and knows all
  26,221,Should I inform you of whom the devils come down on
  26,222,They come down on every lying sinner
  26,223,"who give ear (and listen to the devils), and most of them are liars"
  26,224,"And the poets, the misled ones (those who lost the right way) follow them"
  26,225,Did you not see that they drift into every valley (and subject)
  26,226,and they say what they do not do
  26,227,Except those (poets) who believe and do good works and often remember God and help/defend themselves after they are wronged. And those who do wrong are going to know to what return they will return